Added [tests/deep-link-roundtrip.test.js](/C:/Users/ColsonR/lrsl-driller/tests/deep-link-roundtrip.test.js#L1). It uses the real `apstats-u5-sampling-dist` manifest plus `Platform`/`GameEngine` behavior to cover direct deep-link entry, refresh restoration, locked-mode fallback to the first incomplete prerequisite, and post-entry progression including the `5-7 -> 5-2` regression guard.

The refresh-state test is scoped to persisted progression state (`currentTier`, `starsPerMode`, unlock chain), because the core platform currently persists that state but not in-progress input drafts. I couldn’t run `npx vitest run tests/deep-link-roundtrip.test.js --reporter=verbose` here because Vitest startup is blocked in this sandbox by `esbuild` failing with `spawn EPERM`. I did validate the file syntax with `node --check` and manually replayed representative mode 5, mode 7, and last-mode scenarios against the same harness logic.
